<title>ZIMBABWE: COLCOM RAISES HALF YR SHR, DIV.</title>
<headline>COLCOM RAISES HALF YR SHR, DIV.</headline>
<dateline>HARARE 1996-11-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Half-yr ended September 30.</p>
<p>	    (million Zimbabwe dollars unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr (cts)			     13.01 vs 6.99</p>
<p>    Div (cts)				6.00 vs 2.00</p>
<p>    Operating income		     9.10 vs 6.19</p>
<p>    Net interest			   0.97 vs 0.61</p>
<p>    Shr of associate firm profits    0.81 vs ---</p>
<p>    Pre-tax income			10.89 vs 5.58</p>
<p>    Taxation				 1.79 vs 1.53</p>
<p>    After-tax income		     9.10 vs 4.04</p>
<p>    Turnover				134.3 vs 113.6</p>
<p>Div payable Jan 10</p>
<p>on register Dec 13.</p>
<p>Full name: Colcom Holdings Limited </p>
<p>NOTE:- The group said it expected to perform better in the</p>
<p>second half of the year due to improved volumes and increased</p>
<p>sales of high margin products over the Christmas period.</p>
<p>-- Emelia Sithole, Harare Newsroom: +263-4 72 52 27/8/9</p>
